opensalestax-prestashop — dual license declaration
==================================================

This software is distributed under your choice of either:

* Apache License, Version 2.0 (Apache-2.0)
  — see ``LICENSE-APACHE.txt``, OR
* GNU General Public License, version 2 or later
  (GPL-2.0-or-later) — see ``LICENSE-GPL.txt``.

SPDX expression: ``Apache-2.0 OR GPL-2.0-or-later``.

Recipient picks. Most consumers — including merchants embedding
the module in their own PrestaShop deployment — will find
Apache-2.0 sufficient. The GPL-2.0-or-later option exists so the
module can be redistributed via PrestaShop ecosystems that
require GPL-compatible licensing (PrestaShop core itself is
OSL-3.0 + AFL-3.0; both are GPL-compatible) and to keep the
dual-license footprint consistent across the broader
OpenSalesTax portfolio (the WooCommerce connector ships under
the same expression; the Odoo connector ships
LGPL-3.0-or-later OR AGPL-3.0-or-later for analogous
cross-ecosystem reasons).

Note on PrestaShop module conventions
-------------------------------------

PrestaShop's official module guidelines suggest AFL-3.0 or
OSL-3.0 for marketplace submissions, but neither is mandatory
for self-distributed modules. The Apache-2.0 OR
GPL-2.0-or-later expression is GPL-compatible and OSI-approved;
when this module is later submitted to the PrestaShop Addons
Marketplace (deferred to v0.2+), the recipient may elect the
GPL-2.0-or-later option to satisfy any redistribution
requirements there. See ``specs/decisions/001-license-choice.md``
for the full reasoning.

Contributors agree their contributions are licensed under both
options (see ``CONTRIBUTING.md``).

